Tune in to our livestream on Wednesday, 6 May at 12:00 Eastern Time to hear about what it’s like to do astronomy at the South Pole. Maclean Rouble, Cynthia Chiang, and Josh Montgomery will give a short talk on the unique science that they do at the bottom of the Earth, followed by a Q&amp;A featuring your questions!</p>

<p>If you have a question you would like to ask in advance, please submit it here: https://tinyurl.com/questions-astro We’ll also be taking questions during the livestream via the comments section.</p>

